title: Gabby Petito’s Cause of Death Was by Strangulation, Coroner Says
sub_head: Body of missing New York native was outside for three to four weeks, says Teton County, Wyo., official
body:
Gabby Petito, the 22-year-old woman who went missing over the summer during a road trip, was killed by being strangled, according to the coroner for Teton County, Wyoming.
Ms. Petito’s remains were found last month in Wyoming’s Bridger-Teton National Forest, after the New York native’s family had reported her disappearance, in a case that drew national attention.
